                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="81444" author="tappro" created="Fri, 11 Apr 2014 18:53:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing ticket as it was finished and all sub-tasks were finished too&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56207" author="sarah" created="Fri, 12 Apr 2013 17:06:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Doug,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;About the Grant test, I don&apos;t quite get what you mean, could you please git more detailed information? Thanks in advanced.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the grant part I don&apos;t understand:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Test grant by using currently disabled grant regression sanity tests with ldiskfs OST to ensure grant works fine&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54877" author="doug" created="Tue, 26 Mar 2013 23:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OSD-MDT Feature test plan&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Area of change: use of LOD/OSP instead of LOV/OSC on MDS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;test OST object pre-creation and destroy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Area of change: IO Performance with new obdfilter&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IO performance testing on Hyperion with new obdfilter (OFD) to verify there is no regression on IO performance for this new filter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Area of change: Quota and Grant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Quota being properly tested with test plan for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1920&quot; title=&quot;Create and attach Test Plan for quota testing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1920&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1920&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Test grant by using currently disabled grant regression sanity tests with ldiskfs OST to ensure grant works fine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Area of change: llog&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;use llog_test to verify no regression in performance do to this change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Area of change: DNE changes to MDT/MDD on MDS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;performance regression tests for metadata stack&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Notes for this item:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;it&apos;s better to run on Toro or Rosso, not Hyperion, because Toro and Rosso have much better CPUs (more cores, faster)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;MDS doesn&apos;t require super faster storage as MDT, but it has to have fast journal device, let&apos;s say, SSD or just ramdisk.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;16 client nodes is a good number to generate enough workload on MDS, but if it&apos;s too difficult to get this number, then 12, 10 or even 8 might work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
